The enclosed disk contains a file, MACROS.DOC, that offers several
useful macros.

To use these macros, do the following:

1. Start Word for Windows and from the File menu, choose Open.

2. Insert the enclosed WordBasic Macro Examples disk in drive A or B.

3. In the File Name box, type "a:macros.doc" or "b:macros.doc"
   (without quotation marks) and choose the OK button.

4. Locate the macro name and description you want to install. To
   globally install the macro, select the macro you want and choose
   the Install button. To learn about a macro, select the macro you
   want and choose the About button.

    Note: After each macro installs, a dialog box will appear stating,
    "<macroname> saved to Global successfully." Choose the OK button.
    Another dialog box will appear asking, "Do you want to save
    global, glossary, and command changes?" Choose the Yes button.

The macros that you install using the instructions above can be run by
choosing Macro from the Tools menu, selecting the appropriate macro
name from the Macro Name box, and choosing the Run button.

